United States as Long-Term Holder.

Donald Trump signed an executive order to create a #Bitcoin reserve. A Strategic $BTC Reserve fund with seized Bitcoin and plans to buy more.

This means that the United States’ current Bitcoin holdings of 188,898 BTC ($18.14 billion) will be secured as part of the Strategic Bitcoin Reserve rather than being sold.

This move could significantly reduce potential selling pressure in the future.
